   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of lifesaving cash assistance to households affected by Floods in Sindh, Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide urgent lifesaving cash assistance to households affected by floods in Sindh. This WFP project provides 15,851 households with $1.03 million in cash to meet critical food needs. The project provides life-saving assistance to 50,000 people, including 26,304 women, 27,375 men, over nearly 50,000 children, including 2,576 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
